{"questionId":"33402083","questionHtml":"<p>Show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>2</mn></math>, for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≠</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to write <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>q</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; to write <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math> in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>q</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><em> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Follow through from their part (d).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>q</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></strong>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math><em> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>since&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>7</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≠</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R</strong><strong>1</strong></em><strong><br></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award a maximum of <em><strong>A1M1A0R0</strong></em> for a graphical approach which includes a horizontal asymptote at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>, showing that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/48c7af135616669aa723c491820e65544a99b389.png\"></p>\n<p><br><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>clear assumption that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>≤</mo><mn>2</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>≤</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>⇒</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>≤</mo><mn>8</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>contradiction implies that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>2</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>A1M0A0R0 </strong></em>for solutions which work backwards from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>2</mn></math> to arrive at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>8</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33402083","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.12e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that dydx>2, for x∈ℝ, x≠-2.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}